  "meta": {
    "curriculum": "Zambia",
    "grade": "5",
    "subject": "Zambian Languages",
    "philosophy": "Zambian Languages are vehicles through which most Zambians communicate with each other. Therefore, it is important that learners learn Zambian Languages in order to know how to use the language correctly and appropriately as well to appreciate the technical aspects of the language which cannot be acquired outside formal instruction. Teaching and learning Zambian Languages will enable learners to eventually become experts in translation, interpretation, writing, editing and publishing among others. It will also act as a resource for cultural preservation and increase learners' opportunities for further education.",
    "competence_learning": "The Zambian Languages Upper Primary School Syllabus has been developed to facilitate learning that will promote competences in learners from Grade 4 to 6. It has been designed to equip learners with skills to access, criticise, analyse and practically apply knowledge. The content provided in this syllabus is packaged to stimulate learners in thinking reflectively, logically, creatively, and critically so as to promote the formation of positive social behaviour. The activities provided are aimed at engaging learners in linguistic practice thereby fostering proficiency. Cross-cutting themes and emerging issues such as National Values and Principles, Corruption, Climate Change and Financial Education have been incorporated in the syllabus to ensure that learners are prepared to live responsible lives and be protected from life threatening vices. The syllabus provides content which should allow learners to acquire more advanced competences in listening and speaking, reading fluency, vocabulary use, writing and language structure. It also provides topics and subtopics on customs and traditions because Zambian Languages also carry the culture of the Zambian people.",
    "goals": [
      "To facilitate learning that will promote competences in learners.",
      "To equip learners with skills to access, criticise, analyse and practically apply knowledge.",
      "To nurture effective communication both in speech and writing.",
      "To develop learners as individuals and eventually contribute to the wellbeing of society and the nation as a whole.",
      "To stimulate learners in thinking reflectively, logically, creatively, and critically.",
      "To promote the formation of positive social behaviour.",
      "To engage learners in linguistic practice thereby fostering proficiency.",
      "To ensure that learners are prepared to live responsible lives and be protected from life threatening vices.",
      "To acquire more advanced competences in listening and speaking, reading fluency, vocabulary use, writing and language structure.",
      "To understand customs and traditions as Zambian Languages carry the culture of the Zambian people."
    ]
  },
